==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gapeseed
<hw>Gape"seed`</hw> <pr>(g⟦amac⟧p"s⟦emac⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Any strange sight.</def> <rj><au>Wright.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person who looks or stares gapingly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>To buy gapeseed</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>To
sow gapeseed</b></col></mcol>, <cd>to stare idly or in idle wonderment,
instead of attending to business.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gapesing</ent>⟦br⟧
